{
  "stem": "10587.6",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was raining, it was terrible weather, and cold, and we were parked-- we was-- put there-- and we stood there for quite a while.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Maybe like 100 yards away from us, there was another train with American prisoners, which they were-- they at least had food, Red Cross, and-- and they were treated more human like, at least, till that point.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But they were bombing Dresden at that time, and there was a direct hit on that transport of American prisoners.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And many people were killed, and some of them that survived tried to run away so they could save their life.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- and we-- the wehrmacht-- I think it was wehrmacht-- they set up machine guns under the train and mowed them all down.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was a horrible sight to watch because the Americans were our final solution to stay alive, so we were-- that was a sad moment for the whole transport.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Then we finally-- they shuffled us around, and we finally arrived at this camp called Hersbruck.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That's not far from Nuremberg.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In Hersbruck, they were building-- we were building tunnels, big tunnels, part of them were already tiled, you know, like a-- what-- what is to be a underground factory for the Messerschmitt jet plane, because everything was-- they bombed everything else, so they-- that was what they wanted to do.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So we were-- that was a terrible camp, that Hersbruck, because we walked for quite a while-- at least one hour or two to the camp to the work site.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Walked, right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the same thing in the evening.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then when we come home in the evening, we had to clean up the camp, police the area, and-- and received very little sleep there.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
